acceptance_criteria: Package uses current pm CLI/SDK and pm-changelog; release/check scripts pass; pm items capture decisions; no tracked secrets/private data are introduced; GitHub PR/release state is reviewed.
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-09T21:36:07.996Z",codex-foundation,"2026-07-09 scope checkpoint: inventorying GitHub reports, current PR branch, dependency versions, release automation, package activation, real-workspace behavior, and full-history privacy posture before implementation."
  "2026-07-11T19:01:13.869Z",codex,"Current inspection: no open GitHub PRs/issues or audit vulnerabilities; pm health clean. Found exact duplicate pmc-6kvp (canceled in favor of evidence-rich pmc-yy8d), preferred --pm-path not yet used in generator, and toolchain updates available."
  "2026-07-11T19:05:02.363Z",codex,"Filed https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/516 with a minimal reproduction. Updated integration coverage to assert pm-changelog itself is installed, active, and runtime-active under isolated diagnostics."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-09T21:36:08.218Z",codex-foundation,Toolchain baseline is global pm CLI 2026.7.9. Required package target is @unbrained/pm-cli 2026.7.9 and pm-changelog 2026.7.8 after registry verification. No telemetry/observability changes are authorized.
  "2026-07-11T19:05:59.334Z",codex,"Validated @unbrained/pm-cli 2026.7.11, @types/node 26.1.1, TypeScript 7.0.2. release:check passes all 128 tests, zero audit vulnerabilities, 37-file controlled tarball, and current generated changelog. GitHub Dependabot/secret alerts zero; code scanning not configured. Tracked/full-history credential scans zero; no private host/path patterns in history."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-11T19:05:02.363Z",codex,"pm 2026.7.11 can seed unrelated project-managed packages during plain init despite a fresh PM_GLOBAL_PATH; --isolated then correctly describes those leaked project packages. Upstream issue #516 filed. Package tests must assert the target extension identity/activation, not a machine-dependent aggregate count."
